For Kok Wai, painting serves as an avenue to express himself freely. Kok Wai joined MINDS in 1992 as a production worker in a high support needs group. After an assessment by one of MINDS’ Senior Training Officers, his passion for crafts was discovered. Now, Kok Wai creates paintings for MINDS Craft, one of MINDS Social Enterprise’s eight product lines. Kok Wai’s painting technique of choice? A unique mix of brush strokes and finger dabbing to create intricate textures on his art pieces!

Working at MINDS Craft has not only helped Kok Wai discover his calling for the Arts, it has also allowed him to improve his socialisation skills. Now, he interacts with people confidently and does not hesitate to help when his friends are in need.

@sgminds started MINDS Social Enterprise to empower adults with intellectual disabilities through vocational training and work engagement opportunities. Support MINDS Social Enterprise’s vision to develop and encourage talented trainees like Kok Wai to maximise their potential and to transform society’s perception of their capabilities! Visit https://www.se.minds.org.sg/ to purchase their products and to find out more about this initiative. #InclusiveSG #SeetheTrueMe

